Description. FEMALE. Body reddish brown. Rostrum reaching distal portion of femur I (
Fig. 1
). Palpus (
Fig. 2
) with spinneret about 1.5 times as long as broad; dorsal sensillum (solenidion) fusiform. Peritreme dilated at distal end (
Fig. 4
). Dorsal setae on idiosoma longer than distances between bases of consecutive setae; f 2 about 4 / 5 as long as f 1 (
Fig. 1
). Dorsocentral striae transverse except for V- shaped pattern between and anterior to e 1 setae (
Fig. 1
). Genital flap with transverse striae; area immediately anterior to flap with longitudinal striae.

